title: pt_imp_group
body:
A [[abyssal ship]] enemy type in [[Kantai Collection]].

Representing "PT boats":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PT_boat], which are too small a class for "shipgirlification", they appear as a trio of abyssal [[baby|babies]] or even fetuses whose heads fuse into smaller versions of abyssal destroyer-types, like the [[I-class destroyer]] with large horns. One even has an apparent "[[umbilical cord]]" tube and a black [[diaper]]-like armor.

Like the ships they represent, they carry [[torpedo|torpedoes]] as their primary armament.  In-game they are made to be much harder for larger ships like battleships to hit unless they are armed with secondary guns, as they are meant to represent swarms of tiny coastal craft rather than individual ships. 

They were introduced in the Fall 2015 event, which notably involves battles in the "Solomon Islands Campaign":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Solomon_Islands_campaign where the US tried on several occasions to sink Japanese convoys with PT boat torpedo attacks, usually with unsuccessful results. They were quite successful though at "barge busting", attacking the barges and transports in the littorals as they tried to ferry supplies and reinforcements under the cover of night to avoid Allied air superiority.  This helped to cause severe shortages of supplies and reinforcements for Japanese forces.

Their name can literally be read as "small oni group", so they might be considered similar to "oni-tier" ships.

Notoriously hard to kill for both newer and older admirals. While not extremely powerful when compared to those such as [[wo-class aircraft carrier]] and the newer [[re-class battleship]], they make up in numbers, sometimes coming in pairs and often seen with bosses and the stronger relatives, sometimes both.

title: kuss
body:
A poem by Franz Grillparzer (1791–1872).


[i]Auf die Hände küßt die Achtung,
Freundschaft auf die offne Stirn,
Auf die Wange Wohlgefallen,
Sel'ge Liebe auf den Mund;
Aufs geschloßne Aug' die Sehnsucht,
In die hohle Hand Verlangen,
Arm und Nacken die Begierde;
Überall sonst hin Raserei.[/i]


Respect kisses on the hands,
Friendship on the open forehead,
Delight on the cheek,
Happy love on the mouth;
Longing on the closed eye,
Yearning in the cupped hand,
On arms and neck, desire;
Everywhere else, frenzy.

title: berserker_armor
body:
In [[Berserk]], the Berserker Armor is a cursed suit of [[armor]] that grants its user incredible strength and endurance by allowing its wearer to bypass the normal subconscious limits that prevent him from injuring himself when using his full strength. It can temporarily fix injuries by binding bleeding wounds, reinforcing broken bones and fixing dislocated joints. It can also send its user into a berserker rage where he cannot tell friend from foe. Long-term use of the armor can cause chronic mental deterioration, as well as severe physical effects.

When in Berserker mode, the armor takes on the appearance of the user's inner "beast." For [[Guts (berserk)|]], the current wearer and user of the armor, this is the [[Beast of Darkness (berserk)|]], the demonic hellhound-like wolf that represents all the hatred and evil that dwells within his soul, which becomes stronger every time Guts uses the armor.

title: beast_of_darkness_(berserk)
body:
In [[Berserk]], the Beast of Darkness, also known as the Hellhound, is [[Guts (berserk)|]]' inner beast, the manifestation of all the hatred and evil that has dwelled within his soul since the Eclipse. It takes the form of a great black houndlike wolf with sinister-looking flaming red eyes. It taunts him, questioning the morality of his quest for revenge against [[Griffith (berserk)|]] and urging him to commit ever-greater atrocities, with the ultimate goal of turning him into a monster.

As the Black Swordsman, Guts and the Beast worked in concert, and the path of revenge and bloodshed that Guts walked after the Eclipse allowed the Beast to grow in power. When Guts found [[Casca (berserk)|]] again and started thinking about things other than revenge, the Beast began to work against him, and has begun attempting to convince him to give into his dark desires and kill her so that he can get back to his vendetta against Griffith. The [[Berserker Armor]], though it increases Guts' fighting power against the demonic Apostles that he fights, gives power to the Beast every time he goes into Berserker mode, and only with the help of his newfound friends has Guts managed to keep the Beast at bay.

title: ushiromiya_beatrice
body:
[b]Major spoilers below.[/b]

Character from [[Umineko no Naku Koro ni]].

[spoiler]Ushiromiya Beatrice (often referred to as Kuwadorian Beatrice) was the daughter of [[Ushiromiya Kinzou]] and [[Beatrice Castiglioni]]. Kinzo named her after her mother, who died giving birth to her, claiming Kuwadorian Beatrice to be the reincarnation of his dead lover. She lived in the hidden Kuwadorian mansion on Rokkenjima, where she was raised by [[Kumasawa Chiyo]].

As she grew older, her appearance was strikingly similar to that of her dead mother. Kinzo did not see her as his daughter, and poured his affection onto her, resulting in the birth of [[Yasu_(umineko)|]]/[[ushiromiya_lion|Lion]].

Kuwadorian Beatrice later met her death when [[Ushiromiya Rosa]] chanced upon the mansion and took her outside, where she fell off a cliff and died. She is the basis of the legend of the Golden Witch and is the model for the portrait in the main hall.[/spoiler]

title: black_dragon_(power_rangers)
body:
Black Dragon is a controlled [[mecha|zord-like machine]] from the [[Mighty Morphin Power Rangers]] comic.

The Green Chaos crystal that [[Witch Bandora|Rita Repulsa]] gave Scorpina became charged with green chaos energy it collected from fighting Tommy. When Tommy, Jason, and Zack started arguing at the Command Center, the crystal opened a portal (and blew up half the Center) allowing the Black Dragon to emerge in a gigantic size. He shrunk down and confronted the rangers, offering them a chance to surrender but they refused. He walked right through the rangers, seemingly trying to drain their powers every chance he got. Most of the rangers escaped Black Dragon in the pocket dimension but he managed to grab Billy and knock him out. When Rita and her forces arrived at the wreckage, Black Dragon used Billy's power coin and the Green Chaos crystal to tap directly into the Morphin Grid and absorb Jason, Zack, Trini, and Kimberly's powers.

It later turned out that the Black Dragon was a zord-like machine, reconstructed using parts from the [[Dragonzord]], controlled by [[Lord Drakkon]].

title: fu-ha_jin
body:
Fu-ha Jin is a strange looking ninja first appearing [[Ryuuko no Ken]] Gaiden (Art of Fighting 3). He was a disciple of the Kisaragi school of ninjutsu until he was passed over for [[Kisaragi Eiji]] as the sole successor to be leader. Jin left in anger and decided to wait for his opportunity to destroy Eiji, and at the same time decided to fight Eiji's rival [[Ryou Sakazaki]].

He had little notability until re-discovered by Japanese website Bohyou, which led to the Japanese [[m.u.g.e.n|MUGEN]] community finding him and frequently using him. His odd looking moves and memetic lines led to his popularity as a joke character.

This, in turn, has led him to appear in MUGEN related works such as  [i][[The Iron of Yin and Yang|Touhou - The Iron of Yin and Yang]][/i], where he is the only non-[[Touhou]], non-[[Final Fantasy XI]] character.

title: chris_(kof)
body:
Character from [[the King of Fighters]] series of fighting games.

He is the singer for CYS, a rock band consisting of and named after the initals of himself (C), [[Nanakase Yashiro]] (Y), and [[Shermie (kof)|]] (S).

They seemingly entered [[The King Of Fighters '97|The 1997 King of Fighters tournament]] to take revenge on [[Yagami Iori]] for canceling one or more of their shows, but as the tournament progresses, their Orochi blood awakens, thus remembering their status as the Four Heavenly Kings of [[Orochi_(kof)|]] alongside [[Goenitz]].

Shermie and Yashiro sacrifice themselves to awaken Orochi, who would later use him as a vessel. But Orochi's awakening was short-lived as [[Kusanagi Kyou|Kusanagi Kyo]] (possessing the Sword of the Kusanagi), Iori (possessing the Jewel of Yasakani, and the target of CYS), and [[Kagura Chizuru]] (possessing the Mirror of Yata) combine forces to seal Orochi along with Chris's body.

He fights using speedy attacks in his normal form, and [[purple fire]] as [[Orochi Chris]].

body:
[[The King Of Fighters]] character. She is famous for her hair that is tied into split ponytails with [[Hair over eyes|bangs that cover her eyes]] and large bust. She is tied with [[Angel (kof)|]] for the biggest bust in all of KOF at 92 cm. According to her profile from KOF 10th, she was based on the character [[Mine Fujiko]] from [i][[Lupin III]][/i].

She is the keyboardist for CYS, a rock band consisting of and named after the initals of [[Chris (kof)|]] (C), [[Nanakase Yashiro]] (Y), and herself (S).

They seemingly entered [[The King Of Fighters '97|The 1997 King of Fighters tournament]] to take revenge on [[Yagami Iori]] for canceling one or more of their shows, but as the tournament progresses, their Orochi blood awakens, thus remembering their status as the Four Heavenly Kings of [[Orochi (kof)|]] alongside [[Goenitz]].

She and Yashiro sacrifice themselves to awaken Orochi, who would later use Chris as a vessel. But Orochi's awakening was short-lived as [[Kusanagi Kyou|Kusanagi Kyo]] (possessing the Sword of the Kusanagi), Iori (possessing the Jewel of Yasakani, and the target of CYS), and [[Kagura Chizuru]] (possessing the Mirror of Yata) combine forces to seal Orochi alongside Chris's body.

She fights using grappling moves, especially [[wrestling]] throws, with her specialty being the [[german suplex]] in her normal form, and [[electricity]] as [[Orochi Shermie]].

The Underground is a large area comprised of many corridors located underneath the whole region of Sinnoh, accessible in [i][[Pokemon DPPt|Pokémon Diamond, Pearl and Platinum]][/i].

Multiple players can interact in the Underground via the DS Wireless Communication.

Some activities available in the Undergound include:

* Digging items such as fossils and evolutionary stones from the walls.
* Building and decorating a [[secret_base_(pokemon)|Secret Base]].
* Finding the Secret Bases of other players and capturing their flags.
* Placing traps on the ground, which often negatively affect the movements of players who step on them.

title: dragoon_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[demonic_lancer|Demonic Lancer]]. Also known as the Leviathan or Deimos.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/5/50/Dragonian_Lancer_Art.png] has longer hair, tied into a thin ponytail. He wears a white and navy coat and retains his gray armor from his base class.

As a "Deimos":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/b/be/GenociderPortrait.png], his outfit has been recolored entirely black, with his hair being slightly longer and sporting a thicker ponytail.

title: vanguard_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[demonic_lancer|Demonic Lancer]]. Also known as the Revenant or Warlord.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/5/57/Vanguard_Fullbody.png] features blue Eastern-themed robes with brown accents, and his hair is now shoulder-length. He's also seen wearing gray pauldrons, gauntlets and greaves.

As a "Warlord":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/e/e5/WarlordPortrait.png], his hair is short and swept back, and he wears a black coat with red accents, left unbuttoned at the top revealing an X-shaped scar across his chest. His armor is also now black and gold.

title: elven_knight_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[knight_(dungeon_and_fighter)|Knight]]. Also known as the 1A or 2A.

Her "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/a/a3/Elven_Knight_Full_Body.png] has long, waist-length blonde hair (with some locks styled into curls) and dark green eyes. While her top is fairly similar to her base class, she now wears red thighhighs and gloves along with bronze gauntlets and greaves. Lastly, she wears a white flower in her hair.

As a "Gaia":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/8/80/Gaia.png], her hair is now straight and she wears a frilled white leotard with green accents, green thighhighs, and gray gauntlets and greaves.

title: shadow_dancer_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[rogue_(dungeon_and_fighter)|Rogue]]. Also known as the Nightmare or Grim Reaper.

Her "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/d/d0/ShadowDancer.png] features waist-length hair, a leather jacket and thighhigh boots, a black hooded cape with red ropes and a rose motif on the hood, and a black bodysuit slightly torn in various places.

As a "Grim Reaper":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/2/27/GrimReaper_Fullbody.png], her outfit is mostly the same, save for an extremely long black cape. Her skin has taken on a pale purple tone and her eyes are shadowed underneath.

title: kunoichi_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[rogue_(dungeon_and_fighter)|Rogue]]. Also known as the Izunabi or Shiranui.

Her "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/8/83/KunoichiPortrait.jpg] has her hair styled up into a bun and half-updo. She wears a black leotard and transparent black bodysuit torn in various places, and a pair of black slippers.

As a "Shiranui":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/f/f9/Shiranui_Fullbody.jpg], she wears her hair loose and her skin takes on a light purple tone. She's seen in white robes resembling a short-skirt [[kimono]], white thighhighs, white belts strapped on her thighs holding kunai, red greaves and gauntlets, and a red scarf with orange tips.

title: necromancer_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[rogue_(dungeon_and_fighter)|Rogue]]. Also known as the Defiler or Thanatos.

Her "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/e/e0/NecromancerPortrait.png] has her skin taking on a light purple tone, longer straight hair, a mostly leather black bodysuit with multiple belts on her torso, and black gauntlets and greaves with gold accents. Her main summon, a warrior ghost named Vallacre, is seen hovering behind her.

As a "Thanatos":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/9/95/Thanatos_Fullbody.png], her long hair is styled into curls and she's seen wearing a purple and white dress vest, purple capelet, black stocking and black thighhigh boots. She's seen sitting atop a now-enlarged Vallacre's palm.

title: rogue_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[rogue_(dungeon_and_fighter)|Rogue]]. Also known as the Silver Moon or Alcyone.

Her "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/6/62/RoguePortrait1.png] has her wearing a black tanktop and black pants with hip cutouts. Her white hair is longer and styled into a ponytail.

As an "Alcyone":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/e/e0/Alcyone1.png], she wears a white jacket, black stockings and white boots and sports a rose tattoo on her left cheek. Oddly, her skin is a light purple, a trait that's somewhat common with her fellow Dark Elves.

title: thief_(dungeon_and_fighter)

[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character.

Her "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/b/bd/ThiefPortrait.png] is a young dark-skinned woman with short, white hair, wearing a black jacket and pants, purple dress vest, and a hat with a blue rose attached to it.

title: mistress_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[female_priest_(dungeon_and_fighter)|female Priest]]. Also known as the Sin Sayer or Redeemer.

Her "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/b/b5/Mistress_Portrait.jpg] features her in a backless black robe, exposing the cross tattoo covering her back. She also wears red gloves, a black belt adorned with various jewellery, and black stockings.

As a "Redeemer":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/a/a0/Redeemer_Portrait.jpg], she's seen wearing a black halter top, leather belts along her legs, and an oversized white jacket. Two pairs of white-tipped black wings are seen on her back.

She is capable of transforming into a [[demon_girl|demon]] with longer black hair tied into a ponytail, purple skin, and pointy ears, wearing nothing except arm-length gloves, demon-themed thighhighs and black pasties.

In all of her official appearances, she's seen wielding a scythe, her weapon of choice.

title: shaman_(dungeon_and_fighter)

[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[female_priest_(dungeon_and_fighter)|female Priest]]. Also known as the Oracle or Divineress.

Her "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/c/cb/Shaman_Portrait.jpg] features Eastern-themed white and yellow priestess robes and shoulder-length black hair. Her thighhighs have been replaced with black slippers and yellow ties nearly going up to her knees.

As a "Divineress":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/7/7c/Goddess_Portrait.jpg], part of her hair is tied up into a bun, and her outfit is now predominantly white and red.

title: inquisitor_(dungeon_and_fighter)

title: original_zero
body:
The sub-boss of [[The King of Fighters 2001]]. Fights using 3 strikers ([[Krizalid]], [[Ron (kof)|]], and his pet lion [[Glaugan]])

Unlike [[Zero (KOF)|his clone]], this Zero is extremely loyal to the NESTS syndicate and was disgusted to learn of his clone's attempted coup d'état. He was resting in NESTS's main headquarters during the events of 2000 and was unaware of his clone's actions until later.

He was ordered by the leader of NESTS to resume their primary plan of world conquest. Since the fighting data of the world's fighters had already been gathered and saved in the main database of NESTS's computers, the cartel planned to be rid of them and take over the then helpless planet.

Willing to clear his reputation of his clone's actions, True Zero is commanded to destroy the winners of The King of Fighters tournament. He traps the winning team in a space ship that was disguised as a blimp. He then informs the team about their real destination to NESTS's main headquarters in outer space as well as other information concerning NESTS's intentions.

Upon being defeated by the player, he urges the team to escape the collapsing ship and presumably dies honorably on board the vessel. 

He fights in the same way as his clone was, but he loses his clone's shadow arts in exchange for his strikers.

Voiced by Arai Toshimitsu.

title: omega_rugal
body:
An alternate form of [[Rugal Bernstein]] in [[The King of Fighters '95]]. He is basically a cyborg version of Rugal who now becomes stronger thanks to a pact he made with [[Orochi (kof)|]].

He has then since appeared in dream match games, either as a [[palette swap]] or a recolor of the original Rugal.

The original Rugal and Omega Rugal can be differentiated by their backs. Omega Rugal has what seems to be the jet mufflers that the original Rugal lacks while charging the Kaiser Wave, as well as an [[omega symbol]] engraved on the back of his top.

Their movesets also differ in [[The King of Fighters '98|KOF 98]]. Omega Rugal had the Gravity Smash in exchange for Normal Rugal's Reppuken, the Vanishing Rush in exchange for the Kaiser Wave, and the Destruction Omega in exchange for the Dead End Screamer. Omega Rugal also gains a move that was never used by Normal Rugal: the Rugal Execution.

In [[The King of Fighters 2002|KOF 2002]], Omega Rugal used the same moves as Normal Rugal had in [[The King of Fighters '94|KOF 94]] but with the addition of the Beads Destruction, and the altering between Kaiser Wave, Divine Arrow, and Gravity Smash. He gains a new MAX2 in the form of the Kaiser Phoenix, which is a barrage of Kaiser Waves, Divine Arrows, and Gravity Smashes in one move.
